<h2><span class="mw-headline">Further reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Barbara Drinck, Chung-noh Gross <i>Forced Prostitution in Times of War and Peace</i>, Kleine Verlag, 2007. ISBN-13: 978-3-89370-436-1.</li>
<li>Tanaka, Yuki <i>Japan's Comfort Women: Sexual Slavery and Prostitution During World War II and the US Occupation</i>, London, Routledge: 2002. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0415194016" class="internal">ISBN 0-415-19401-6</a>.</li>
<li>Molasky, Michael S. <i>American Occupation of Japan and Okinawa</i>, Routledge, 1999. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0415191947" class="internal">ISBN 0-415-19194-7</a>, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0415260442" class="internal">ISBN 0-415-26044-2</a>.</li>
<li>D. Kim-Gibson, <i>Silence Broken: Korean Comfort Women</i>, 1999. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0931209889" class="internal">ISBN 0-931209-88-9</a>.</li>
<li>Schellstede, Sangmie Choi. <i>Comfort Women Speak: Testimony by Sex Slaves of the Japanese Military</i>, 2000. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0841914133" class="internal">ISBN 0-8419-1413-3</a>.</li>
<li>Wakabayashi, Bob Tadashii "Comfort Women: Beyond Litigious Feminism"</li>
<li>Nora Okja Keller "Comfort Woman", London, Penguin: 1998. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0140263357" class="internal">ISBN 0-14-026335-7</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Maria_Rosa_Henson" title="Maria Rosa Henson" class="mw-redirect">Maria Rosa Henson</a> "Comfort woman: Slave of destiny", Philippine Center for Investigative Journalism: 1996. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9718686118" class="internal">ISBN 9718686118</a>.</li>
</ul>
